{"questionId":"9070099","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Oseltamivir (Tamiflu) and zanamivir (Relenza) are antiviral drugs used to prevent flu.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the names of <strong>two</strong> functional groups that <strong>both</strong> compounds contain, using section&nbsp;37 of the data booklet.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Any two of:</em></p>\n<p>amido</p>\n<p>ether</p>\n<p>carbonyl</p>\n<p><em>Accept “amide/carboxamide”.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept “alkenyl/alkene”.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept “amino/amine”.</em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[Max 2 Marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070099","referenceCode":"17N.3.sl.TZ0.19a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the names of two functional groups that both compounds contain, using section 37 of the data booklet.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.5 Anti-viral medications","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}